            "physical_description": "Watered steel blade inlaid with gold; steel quillon and mounts, inlaid with gold; scales walrus ivory (?); scabbard wood with stamped leather; silver chape inlaid with niello.\n[Sword] Watered steel sword blade (shamshir) with steel mounts inlaid with gold. Verses and inscriptions are inlaid on each side of the blade. Along the back edge is inlaid a genealogy of Shah Tahmasp (1524-76). The blade has been shortened and the profile altered at some point\n[Sheath] Sheath for a sword (shamshir) of  black tooled leather later than the blade, but with watered steel mounts inlaid with gold contemporary with the hilt", 
